Include test logs in JUnit XML output for all tests, not just failures.

Upstream rules_go only attaches test output to the JUnit XML report when a test fails. We need logs for passing tests too, for CI aggregation and debugging flaky tests.

Also switches XML output encoding from CDATA to chardata because CDATA cannot represent all of the emitted output safely in XML 1.0.

This port keeps the generator change from the internal patch and extends the local xmlreport test so this fork proves the passing system-out behavior directly.

